To execute all tests:
    --> pytest

To execute specific test that contains a particular string:
    --> pytest -k <substring> -v

---------------------------------------
### Grouping Tests ###

What Are Markers Used For?
    - To set various features and attributes to test functions.


    $ pytest --markers
        @pytest.mark.env(name)
        @pytest.mark.filterwarnings(warning)
        @pytest.mark.skip(reason=None)
        @pytest.mark.skipif(condition, ..., *, reason=...)
        @pytest.mark.xfail(condition, ..., *, reason=..., run=True, raises=None, strict=xfail_strict)
        @pytest.mark.parametrize(argnames, argvalues)
        @pytest.mark.usefixtures(fixturename1, fixturename2, ...)
        @pytest.mark.tryfirst
        @pytest.mark.trylast